<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE concept PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Concept//EN" "concept.dtd">
<concept id="main_screen">
    <title>Main Screen</title>
    <conbody>
        <p>The main screen allows you to perform system scans, run virus database updates, and configure settings such as scheduled virus scans.</p>
        <fig>
            <image href="../images/main_screen.png" width="500" alt="ClamWin's Main Screen"></image>
        </fig>
        <p>You can open the main console from the start menu, or the windows Task Bar.</p>
        <p>The following table describes the actions available in <ph conkeyref="ClamWinVARS/short_product_name"/>'s main screen</p>
        <table frame="all" rowsep="1" colsep="1" id="table_ywy_3c4_nvb">
            <tgroup cols="2">
                <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*"/>
                <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="3*"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <p>Action</p>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <p>Description</p>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry><p>Update virus database files.</p></entry>
                        <entry><p>Click <uicontrol>Starts Internet Update</uicontrol> (<image href="../images/manual_update_button.png" width="16"></image>) to manually update <ph conkeyref="ClamWinVARS/short_product_name"></ph>'s virus database files.</p>
                        <p>For more information see (link to topic)</p></entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry><p>Scan for virus and malware</p></entry>
                        <entry>
                            <note type="important">
                                <p>By default, <ph conkeyref="ClamWinVARS/short_product_name"></ph> does not clean any virus or malware found during a scan.</p>
                                <p>For more information, see [link to settings]</p>
                            </note>
                            <p>
                                <ph conkeyref="ClamWinVARS/short_product_name"></ph> allows you to perform scans of files, folders and programs executing in your computer.
                            </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <p><b>Full system scan</b>: Select the drive where your operating system is installed and click <uicontrol>Scan Selected Files for Virus</uicontrol> (<image href="../images/scan_file_button.png" width="16"></image>)</p>
                                    <note type="tip"><p>Windows is typically installed in the C: drive.</p></note>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p><b>Scan a file, folder, or external drive</b>: Select the file or folder you want to scan and click <uicontrol>Scan Selected Files for Virus</uicontrol> (<image href="../images/scan_file_button.png" width="16"></image>)</p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p><b>Scan process and programs</b>: bla bla bla (<image href="../images/scan_memory_button.png" width="16"></image>)</p>
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>For more information about scanning for viruses, see [link to topic]</p>
                    </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry><p>Check for program updates</p></entry>
                        <entry><p>Go to <menucascade><uicontrol>Help</uicontrol><uicontrol>Check Latest Version</uicontrol></menucascade> to verify if you have the latest version of <ph conkeyref="ClamWinVARS/short_product_name"></ph></p></entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry><p>Open the settings screen</p></entry>
                        <entry>
                            <p>Configure all of <ph conkeyref="ClamWinVARS/short_product_name"></ph>'s settings, such as scanning options, email alerts or scheduled scans.</p>
                            <p>For more information, see [link to topic]</p>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </conbody>
</concept>
